    "language_filter_contract": "voices without an explicit `languages` field are assumed to support the default_language only ('en'). Voices that work in multiple languages declare languages: ['en', 'he', ...]. The V4 picker (services/v4/VoiceAcquisition.js) filters by the persona's language BEFORE gender + uniqueness when story.language is set.",
    "hebrew_voice_strategy": {
      "phase_a_current": "6 of the existing English-base premade voices are tagged languages: ['en','he'] because they render Hebrew with acceptable quality via fal-ai/elevenlabs/tts/eleven-v3 + language_code='he' (eleven-v3 supports 70+ languages including Hebrew; multilingual-v2 does NOT). Quality: decent — accent inflection is mid-Atlantic-leaning rather than Israeli-native, but the prosody and intelligibility are usable for prestige TV Hebrew dialogue.",
      "phase_b_recommended": "When the user has access to ElevenLabs Voice Library (paid tier), curate 6 Hebrew-native voices with declared languages: ['he'] and add them to this file alongside the existing premade entries. The picker automatically prefers single-language native voices over multi-language base voices when a Hebrew pool exists.",
      "phase_b_acceptance_criteria": [
        "≥ 3 male + ≥ 3 female Hebrew-native voices in the library",
        "spanning age (young_adult / middle_aged / old)",
        "spanning register (warm / neutral / clipped / theatrical)",
        "tag_responsive audit completed against full eleven-v3 tag taxonomy"
      ]
    }
  },
